article.headline: Manhattan 78, Canisius 71
article.story: NEW YORK (AP) -- Arturo Dubois had 18 points and nine rebounds and Manhattan overcame an early 18-point deficit to beat Canisius 78-71 on Friday night, the Jaspers' 11th victory in their last 12 games. Manhattan (11-5, 7-1) fell behind 21-3 and had only one field goal in the first 8:01. The Jaspers gradually reduced the deficit and ran off 13 of the last 18 points in the opening half to pull to 36-30. Manhattan used an 8-0 run to take a 62-60 lead, with Kenny Minor scoring the final six points of the spree. He converted a three-point play and made a 3-pointer. John Popofski responded with a pair of foul shots for Canisius (4-12, 3-5) to produce the first of three second-half ties. The Jaspers finally went ahead for good when Dubois put in a one-hander to make it 70-68 with 2:57 to play. Kevin Downey pulled the visitors to 74-71 on a driving score, but Devon Austin countered with a pair of free throws to increase the Jaspers' advantage to 76-71 with 29.7 seconds remaining. Downey led the Golden Griffins with 16 points. C.J. Anderson added 15 points and 13 rebounds for Manhattan. Popofski finished with 15 points, and Corey Herring added 13 for the Golden Griffins, who lost their fourth consecutive game.
